<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="51">
We examined the illustration of the type and the male and female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Hippia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hippia mumetes" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mumetes">Hippia mumetes</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Cramer, [1775]</bibRefCitation>
), the type species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Hippia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hippia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hippia</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Moeschler, HB" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="8" pageNumber="59" pagination="629 - 700" title="Beitraege zur Schmetterlingsfauna von Surinam." volume="27" year="1878">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Möschler">Moeschler</normalizedToken>
(1878)
</bibRefCitation>
. Those examinations show that the North American species, placed in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Hippia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hippia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hippia</taxonomicName>
, are not congeneric with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Hippia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hippia mumetes" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mumetes">Hippia mumetes</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
